Been there.  I farmed that shit out, was worth throwing money at the problem rather than DIY'ing it, even though my wife got on me about paying someone when I could do it blindfolded

&amp;#x200B;

On the lock front, I'm stuck with August because the property management company that I pay to "Higgins" (maintain, clean, stock the fridge before we transition to them, etc.) my various properties when I'm not in them which, for most of them, is most of the year, August is the only smart lock company they use and I don't want hard keys floating around.
